<P>
   ATTN: Religion editors
</P>
<P>
   Gayle White, religion writer of The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution, will be in Salt Lake City next week covering
the Southern Baptist Convention, which will consider amending its
denominational statement of faith, untouched in 35 years, to add a
definition of marriage as between a man and a woman, and a
statement that a woman should be submissive to her husband. Daily
stories will be filed, including spot coverage of the election of a
new president, probably Tuesday for Wednesday. Paige Patterson,
president of Southeastern Seminary in Wake Forest, N.C., is running
and, barring a huge surprise and a nomination of someone else from
the floor, is likely to be elected. The significance of this is
that Patterson is generally credited with being one of two men who
planned the conservative resurgence in the SBC. A Q&AMP;A with
Patterson is available from Cox News Service.
</P>
