.
</HEADLINE>
  
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``l'' lifestyle news file. For questions, contact Jimmy Johnson
at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
DOG-RENT (Los Angeles) _ Need a doggy for a day? A furry buddy to
play Frisbee with? A sociable canine to help you meet girls? The
unique Rent-A-Dog program at Camp Happy Dog, a day care center for
dogs in Sherman Oaks, may be just the answer. By Carol Bidwell. 
. 
DOG-CAMP (Los Angeles) _ Call it doggy daycare. While the canines
are at Camp Happy Dog, they get groomed, fed, trained, taken for
walks _ and fat dogs are walked on a treadmill. By Carol Bidwell. 
. 
HOT-TIPS _ (Los Angeles) _ Open wide, prepare for impact. New from
Nestles is the Armageddon Asteroid filled with tangy red and black
meteorites and the Chocolate Chain Reaction bar, with exploding
bits inside. By Barbara De Witt. 
. 
. 

