<P>
   SCHOOL-PRAYER-NYT (Washington) _ For the first time in more than
a quarter of a century, the House on Thursday debated _ and
rejected _ an attempt by religious conservatives to amend the
Constitution to allow organized prayer in public schools. By
Katharine Q. Seelye. Moved 6-4.
