scrutiny for its possible role in aiding the escape of pro-Nazi
Croatian leaders after World War II. A new report by the State
Department says Catholic priests in Rome helped Croatian leaders,
who sent up to 700,000 Serbs, Jews and others to death camps, to
hide in Italy after the war and eventually flee to South America.
By Alessandra Stanley. Moved 6-3.
</P>
