<P>
   MARLINS-KOTSAY _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ If he watches the
College World Series, he must do so with greater interest than
most, knowing that he once owned it. Mark Kotsay, the Marlins'
right fielder, was a sophomore center fielder/relief pitcher on the
Cal State-Fullerton baseball team when they went to Omaha for the
1995 World Series. By the time he left Rosenblatt Stadium, he had
led Fullerton to the title, broken or tied six offensive records,
and been called ``the Messiah'' by an opposing coach. Not a bad
week. (Graziano, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
