Ahmed Yassin, the spiritual leader of the militant Hamas movement,
has been received almost like a head of state by nearly a dozen
Islamic countries. Most analysts agree that the warm reception
Yassin has received represents a fresh challenge to Arafat's rule.
By DEBORAH HORAN. (Already filed)
