<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-STATES-AWARDS-PA </SLUG>

<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;  PA Contract Awards States News Service Washington, June 5 --
Fumanti Construction Co. of Old Forge won a $381,100 contract from
the Army in Tobyhanna for property maintenance and repair.
</P>
<P>
   Boeing Helicopters of Ridley Park won a $59,109 contract from
the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for aircraft
components and accessories.
</P>
<P>
   Mount Valley Farms and Lumber of Biglerville won a $64,720
contract from the Defense Industrial Supply Center in Philadelphia
for materials handling equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Mundis Inc. of York won a $116,308 contract from the Defense
Distribution Center in Philadelphia for natural resources and
conservation services.
</P>
<P>
   Advanced Automation Associates Inc. of Exton won a $200,000
contract from the Army in Seattle for property maintenance and
repair.
</P>
<P>
   Treen Box and Pallet Corp. of Bensalem won a $95,640 contract
from the Defense Industrial Supply Center in Philadelphia for
materials handling equipment.
</P>
<P>
   CK Composites Inc. of Mount Pleasant won a $54,000 contract from
the Navy in Philadelphia for communication equipment.
</P>
<P>
   SPD Technologies of Philadelphia won a $79,134 contract from the
Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for circuit breakers.
</P>
<P>
   CCI Construction of Mechanicsburg won a $13.6 million contract
from the Property &AMP; Fiscal Office in Springfield, Ill., for
construction services.
</P>
<P>
   Thermal Flux Corp. of Horsham won a $75,000 contract from the
General Service Administration in Fort Worth, Texas, for tires and
tubes.
</P>
<P>
   Grip-Flex Corp. of Philadelphia won a $63,684 contract from the
Defense Personnel Support Center in Philadelphia for textiles.
</P>
<P>
   Mundis Inc. of York won a $116,308 contract from the Defense
Distribution Center in New Cumberland for natural resources and
conservation services.
</P>
<P>
   -30-
</P>
</TEXT>
