<SLUG> BC-NY-LIBRARY-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OFF TO WORLDS OLD AND NEW, ONLINE 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Last month, the New York Public Library started up
its Digital Library Collections Web site
(http://www.digital.nypl.org).
</P>
<P>
   Readers who click on Digital Schomburg, a collection of more
than 56 texts and 500 images relating to 19th- and 20th-century
African-American history and culture, for example, can view
photographs like one taken in the 1880s by George Brown. Also
available online is a collection of images of New York City during
the Depression taken by Berenice Abbott for the Federal Art
Project, including ``Blossom Restaurant, 103 Bowery, Oct. 24,
1935.''
</P>
<P>
   Within the next two years the library plans to make thousands of
other digitized books, manuscripts, photographs and engravings
available as well as audio and video recordings. It will add six
more collections, including images of early American dance, music
and theater; texts and illustrations revolving around the theme of
marriage and morality in the United States and Britain from 1815 to
1914, the history of the Hudson River Valley in the 19th century
and the development of railroads.
</P>
</TEXT>
