<HEADLINE>
THE BROTHERS HERNANDEZ 
</HEADLINE>
  (lh) 
 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ With the Florida Marlins in town to play the Yankees,
Orlando Hernandez has had a chance to spend time with his younger
half-brother, Livan Hernandez, who made his own mark as a starting
pitcher last year in the World Series.
</P>
<P>
   ``We talked about everything, but not much baseball,'' Livan
Hernandez said Friday. He arrived in New York early enough on
Wednesday night to see Orlando pitch the final two innings of his
winning major league debut.
</P>
<P>
   The Yankee Hernandez will make his second start in the place of
David Cone on Tuesday in Montreal, if Cone's cut right index finger
has not sufficiently healed by then.
</P>
</TEXT>
